Package: picam-frontend
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Web UI + WebRTC relay for one or more picam-orchestrator backends (Go)
 Single web UI for viewing and controlling one or more picam-orchestrator
 backends (each on its own Pi). Serves a single-page browser UI, proxies
 status JSON and control commands (camera switch, OSD toggle, annotation
 toggle) to whichever Pi is selected, and relays WebRTC (VP8) media and
 signaling between browsers and the selected Pi's picam-orchestrator — the
 browser only ever talks to picam-frontend, never directly to a Pi.
 .
 WebRTC media is peer-to-peer by nature, which would otherwise break that
 guarantee — so this process is a small SFU-lite relay, not just a byte
 proxy for the media path: it terminates WebRTC with each browser viewer
 AND with each picam-orchestrator backend, forwarding raw RTP packets
 between them. One upstream connection per (Pi, stream) pair is shared
 across every browser watching that combination.
 .
 This is a from-scratch Go reimplementation of the original C++
 picam-frontend, with the same config file format and HTTP endpoint
 surface — see its README for the full behavioral spec. WebRTC is provided
 by the pure-Go pion/webrtc (no vendored libdatachannel/OpenSSL build
 step).
 .
 Config: /etc/picam-frontend/config.ini
